TrackableImageTrackingModeANDROID :: enum c.int {
	DYNAMIC = 1, // This mode has the highest accuracy and allows low latency tracking of moving images. It has also has the highest power consumption.
	STATIC = 2, // This mode should be used for images that are known to be static or semi-static. This mode leads to less power consumption in comparison to the dynamic mode. If a static image is being moved, it will be updated with a much higher latency than using the dynamic mode.
}

